containing.description:
Returns true if a list contains a value
Parameters:
- value(object) The value to check is in the list

containingall.description:
Returns true if a list contains all values in a second list
Parameters:
- list_two(list) The second list to check if every element is in the first list

defined.description: Return true if the variable is defined

divisibleby.description:
Returns true if a variable is divisible by a number
Parameters:
- divisor(number) The number to check whether a number is divisible by

equalto.description:
Returns true if an object has the same value as another object
Parameters:
- other(object) Another object to check equality against

even.description: Returns true if the value is even

iterable.description: Return true if the object is iterable (sequence, dict, etc)

lower.description: Return true if the given string is all lowercase

mapping.description: Return true if the given object is a dict

none.description: Return true if the given object is null / none

number.description: Return true if the object is a number

odd.description: Return true if a number is an odd number

sameas.description:
Return true if variable is pointing at same object as other variable
Parameters:
- other(object) A second object to check the variables value against

sequence.description: Return true if the variable is a sequence. Sequences are variables that are iterable.

string.description: Return true if object is a string

string_containing.description:
Return true if object is a string which contains a specified other string
Parameters:
- check(string) A second string to check is contained in the first string

string_startingwith.description:
Return true if object is a string which starts with a specified other string
Parameters:
- check(string) A second string to check is the start of the first string

undefined.description: Return true if object is undefined

upper.description: Return true if string is all uppercased

within.description:
Returns true if a value is within a list
Parameters:
- list(list) A list to check if the value is in.
